            @BeautifulLoser- Don't be ignorant. Gnabry was injured a lot at Arsenal hence had only a few opportunities. Arsene obviously saw he was talented, which is why he signed him in the first place, and he actually wanted to keep him but Serge wanted to leave. Arsene never stands in the way of a player who wants to leave providing the transfer fee is fair, be it Overmars, Vieira, Henry, whoever. Also, Bremen bought him outright and have denied that Bayern actually paid any money. There may or may not be a deal in place to sell Gnabry for cheap to Bayern but if there is no legal contract between the 2 clubs in place, Bremen could easily turn round and up the price. It isn't a case of Munich owning him and loaning to Bremen. It is most likely a verbal non-binding agreement of sorts between the 2 clubs which can easily be got around if Gnabry develops into a top player. Long way to go for that anyway.
